"'''The Devil Cried'''" is a song by [[Rock music|rock]] band [[Black Sabbath]] featured on the compilation [[Black Sabbath: The Dio Years]].<ref>http://allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&token=&sql=10:3pfwxzy5ldde</ref> The song peaked on the Hot Mainstream Rock Tracks at 38.<ref>http://allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&searchlink=BLACK|SABBATH&sql=11:gifoxqw5ldse~T51</ref> It was one of three new recordings the group did for the compilation (the others being "Shadow of The Wind" and "Ear In the Wall").<ref>http://www.rhino.com/store/ProductDetail.lasso?Number=116668</ref> [[Tony Iommi]] has called the song, "a mid-tempo track which is... riff-based again, great vocals and I think that's really good."<ref>http://www.metaleater.com/interviews-heavenandhell022007.php</ref>

